From: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Wed, 3 Dec 2025 10:19:53 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] clk: mxl: Fix i2c0 clk gate entry flags

The i2c0 bus is used for communication between the SoC and PMIC by the
Power Management Unit (PMU), also called Energy Processing Unit (EPU).

The clock must not be disabled, otherwise the system will crash. That's
why we set the flag CLK_IGNORE_UNUSED.

Fixes: d058fd9e8984 ("clk: intel: Add CGU clock driver for a new SoC")
Signed-off-by: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
---
 drivers/clk/x86/clk-lgm.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/x86/clk-lgm.c b/drivers/clk/x86/clk-lgm.c
index e1a4fcfda8f4..9f319f5809a5 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/x86/clk-lgm.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/x86/clk-lgm.c
@@ -306,7 +306,7 @@ static const struct lgm_clk_branch lgm_branch_clks[] = {
 		 G_EBU_SHIFT, 0, 0),
 	LGM_GATE(LGM_GCLK_PWM, "g_pwm", NULL, 0, CGU_GATE1,
 		 G_PWM_SHIFT, 0, 0),
-	LGM_GATE(LGM_GCLK_I2C0, "g_i2c0", NULL, 0, CGU_GATE1,
+	LGM_GATE(LGM_GCLK_I2C0, "g_i2c0", NULL, CLK_IGNORE_UNUSED, CGU_GATE1,
 		 G_I2C0_SHIFT, 0, 0),
 	LGM_GATE(LGM_GCLK_I2C1, "g_i2c1", NULL, 0, CGU_GATE1,
 		 G_I2C1_SHIFT, 0, 0),
